	(221,1,'2016-03-01 16:48:30','2016-03-01 16:48:30','<h2>Bring warmth and comfort to your home with electric heat.\r\n<small>Install off-peak electric heating equipment and receive off-peak incentive</small></h2>\r\nAny new off-peak electric heating equipment purchased after May 1. 2014 qualifies for an off-peak electric heat incentive.\r\n\r\nMembers will receive $20 per kilowwatt (kW) for qualifying electric heating equipment with a maximum incentive of $600. The electric equipment must be part of an off-peak heating system with a qualified backup heating source. The equipment must be hard wired.\r\n\r\nHeat pumps may also qualify for the incentive. Air-source heat pumps will receive a $100 per ton incentive. Ground-source heat pumps will receive a $200 per ton incentive. Heat pumps do not have to be controlled as a part of an off-peak system. Any resistance or strip heat as part of a ground-soure heating system must be controlled. The maximum incentive for heat pump is $600.\r\n\r\nThis off-peak installation incentive is in addition to the conservation incentives offered as part of the Cooperative\'s Power Saves Program.\r\n\r\nIn the wake of rising and fluctuating fossil fuel prices and with the electric heating equipment incentives, now is a great time to install off-peak electric heat.\r\n\r\nEquip your home or place of business with a dual-fuel heating system and be set for heating seasons of the future. Call Red Lake Electric Cooperative at 218-253-2168 or 800-245-6068 for more information.\r\n<h2>Qualifying electric heating equipment</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Radiant Underfloor Heat</li>\r\n	<li>Slab Storage - Electric Cable</li>\r\n	<li>Slab Storage - Electric Panels</li>\r\n	<li>Slab Storage - Electric Boiler</li>\r\n	<li>Air-Source Heat Pump</li>\r\n	<li>Ground-Source Heat Pump</li>\r\n	<li>ETS Furnace</li>\r\n	<li>Baseboard Heater</li>\r\n	<li>Boiler</li>\r\n	<li>Cove Heater</li>\r\n	<li>Forced Air Furnace</li>\r\n	<li>Plenum Heater</li>\r\n	<li>Unit Heater</li>\r\n	<li>ETS Room Unit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://gigazonegaming.local/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/ElectricHeating2013.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to view our <strong>Electric Heating Today</strong> </a>publication to view your heating and cooling options.','Electric Heat','','publish','open','open','','electric-heat','','','2016-03-01 17:15:20','2016-03-01 17:15:20','',90,'http://gigazonegaming.local/auto-draft/',0,'post','',0),
