	(286,1,'2016-03-01 20:07:44','2016-03-01 20:07:44','You will receive your energy bill on or near the 9th of each month.\r\n\r\nPayment of your monthly energy bill is due on the 25th of the month.  You may pay your bill in person at RLEC during office hours, use the 24-hour drive-up drop box located next to the RLEC office, by <a href=\"http://gigazonegaming.local/member-services/auto-pay/\">Auto Pay</a>, online at <a href=\"https://www.cps4rec.com/redlake/\" target=\"_blank\">Bill4U</a> or by mail.  Payment must be in the office, drop box, Auto Pay, or in the mail, as evidenced by the postmark, by the 25th day of the following month to avoid a late payment charge.  A 1-1/2% monthly late payment charge will be computed on delinquent energy bills, the minimum late payment charge will be $1.00.\r\n\r\nIf your payment is not received by the 17th of the next month, a final notice of disconnection statement will be included on your following bill.  The final notice statement will notify you when your electric service will be disconnected if the delinquent amount remains unpaid.  If an employee is sent to disconnect your electric service, a $60 collection fee will be charged to your account, even if you pay the collector.\r\n\r\nTo have a disconnected service reconnected, all amounts owing, a $60 reconnection fee, and a security deposit must be paid.  If the service must be reconnected after normal working hours, a $120 reconnection fee must be paid.\r\n<h2>BAD CHECKS</h2>\r\nA $15 charge will be levied each time a check is returned because of nonsufficient funds, account being closed or payment stopped.','Billings and Collection','','inherit','closed','closed','','262-revision-v1','','','2016-03-01 20:07:44','2016-03-01 20:07:44','',262,'http://gigazonegaming.local/%postpath%/262-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(287,1,'2016-03-01 20:08:36','2016-03-01 20:08:36','Payment of your monthly energy bill is due on the 25th of the month. Payment must be in the office or in the mail as evidenced by the postmark by the 25th day of the following month. A 1 1/2% monthly service charge will be computed on delinquent energy bills, the minimum service charge will be $1.00.','Late Payment Policies','','inherit','closed','closed','','265-revision-v1','','','2016-03-01 20:08:36','2016-03-01 20:08:36','',265,'http://gigazonegaming.local/%postpath%/265-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(288,1,'2016-03-01 20:10:13','2016-03-01 20:10:13','Agricultural Sales Tax Exemption\n\nRed Lake Electric Customers can find the MN Agricultural sales tax exemption form at the above link.  Please complete the form and send to:  Red Lake Electric Cooperative, P.O. Box 430, Red Lake Falls, MN   56750.\n\nElectric Heat Sales Tax Exemption\n\nElectricity sold for residential use is not taxable for the months of November through April when sold to customers who use it as their primary source of residential heat.  Primary source of residential heat is the source that supplies more heat than any other source for the largest period of time during the heating season.','Sales Tax Credits','','inherit','closed','closed','','268-autosave-v1','','','2016-03-01 20:10:13','2016-03-01 20:10:13','',268,'http://gigazonegaming.local/%postpath%/268-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
